Boot options for installation include:

Local installation DVD or USB flash drive (physical or ISO image) with no
   network connection required
Local boot CD or USB flash drive (physical or ISO image) with network access
   to a package source
PXE boot using remote DHCP server, remote installer media, remote package
   source, and Kickstart configuration

Possible RHEL installation package sources are:

Local DVD, CD, or USB flash drive (physical or ISO image file)
Repo accessible by FTP
Repo accessible by HTTP
Repo accessible by NFS
